<DocsLayout title="Installation — Kobbe" description="Deploy Kobbe to your Cloudflare account.">
  <h1>Installation</h1>
  <p>
    Kobbe runs on Cloudflare Workers with a D1 database. You need a
    Cloudflare account and <code>wrangler</code> CLI installed.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Clone the repository</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/michael-andreuzza/analytics.git kobbe
cd kobbe
pnpm install</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Create a D1 database</h2>
  <pre><code>wrangler d1 create analytics</code></pre>
  <p>
    Copy the database ID into your <code>wrangler.toml</code> under
    <code>[[d1_databases]]</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Run migrations</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm run db:migrate:local   # local development
pnpm run db:migrate:remote  # production</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Deploy</h2>
  <pre><code>pnpm run deploy</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Add the tracker to your site</h2>
  <p>
    Include the tracker script on every page you want to track.
    Replace <code>YOUR_KOBBE_URL</code> with the URL where you deployed Kobbe.
  </p>
  <pre><code>&lt;script
  defer
  data-api="YOUR_KOBBE_URL/api/collect"
  src="YOUR_KOBBE_URL/tracker.js"
&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>That's it — visit your dashboard to see real-time traffic.</p>
</DocsLayout>
